The paper discusses the reliability, availability, and security of data stored in a Distributed Storage System (DSS) using a data distribution concept and codes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also discusses the functioning of DSS, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses security in the DSS, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Cybersecurity). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different codes in the DSS, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
